Job Summary:  Under limited guidance, works at the business unit level developing the end-to-end solution architecture for significant initiatives in partnership with key business and IT stakeholders. Expose current state architecture and identify options for future state architecture. Works closely with business and IT stakeholders creating solutions that balance competing interests and concerns. Develop plans for and facilitate the migration from current to selected future state by providing technical leadership to multiple initiatives. Mentor those in less senior positions. 
 
 Duties/Responsibilities:  Serves as a solutions expert, at the business unit level developing the most advanced solution architecture for highly complex and significant initiatives in partnership with key business and IT stakeholders. Expose current state architecture and identify options for future state architecture. Works closely with business and IT stakeholders creating solutions that balance competing interests and concerns. Develop plans for and facilitate the migration from current to selected future state by providing technical leadership to multiple initiatives. Mentor those in less senior positions. 
Work at all levels of portfolio and across multiple Agile Release Trains to deliver solution designs 
Present technical approaches to senior leadership team, provide technical leadership at the solution train layer, participate in backlog management, prioritize and estimate work efforts/features/capabilities 
Manage competing priorities 
Effectively communicate architecture, design considerations cross-functional team members and management. 
Foster safe and open communication environment 
Clearly articulate needs to onsite and offshore vendor teams 
Mentor and train people in junior positions 
 
Abilities/Knowledge/Skills Considered a Plus: 
 
Languages: Java, J2EE, and associated components 
Frameworks/Platforms: Renewal frameworks such as Springboot, Pivotal Cloud Foundry, Continuous Integration frameworks such as JaCoCo/Emma, PMD, Jenkins/Hudson 
Build Frameworks: Maven or Gradle 
SCM: VSS/SourceAnywhere, GIT, GITLab etc 
ApplicationMiddleware: WebLogic/Tomcat/JBoss 
Comm Protocols: SOAP, REST, JMS 
Databases: Oracle/No SQL 
OS: Unix/Linux, Shell Scripting 
Unit Testing Frameworks: jUnit/TestNG, EasyMock/Mockito 
Architecture & design Frameworks/Tools: TOGAF, EA-SPARX, Case Complete 
Knowledge of SAFe/Agile 
Data Analytics and IOT 
Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning algorithms 
Work with Enterprise Architects to breakdown EPICs into capability and Business features, define the solution designs, iterate with domain and other solution architects and help guide application architects for Program Level decomposition and robust architectures. 
Facilitate communication and problem solving in large cross-group development. 
Leadership, proactive and excellent communication, presentation, and facilitation skills 
 
Domicile:  This position will be domiciled in Collierville, TN, Colorado Spring, CO, Dallas, TX, Pittsburg, PA and Orlando, FL. 
 
 Remote Work:  The ability to work remotely within the United States may be available based on business need. 
 
 Relocation:  Relocation assistance may be available based on business need. 
 
 Minimum Qualifications:  Bachelor's degree in computer science, engineering, information Systems, business and/or equivalent formal training or work experience. Five (5) years equivalent work experience in information technology or engineering environment. A related advanced degree may offset the related experience requirement. Ability to lead, working collaboratively and creatively with business and IT stakeholders. Strong human relation and communication skills. 
 
 Application Criteria: To be considered, please upload a copy of your current resume to include beginning and ending dates for each employer/position and answer job screening questionnaire by close of business (5:00 PM CST) on Friday, May 14, 2021. 
